raise capital privately avoiding direct equity investment from the uk government which was offered to boost its capital ratio barclays believed that maintaining its independence from government was in the best interests of its shareholders in july  barclays attempted to raise £ billion through a nontraditional rights issue to shore up its weakened tier  capital ratio which involved a rights offer to existing shareholders and the sale of a stake to sumitomo mitsui banking corporation only  of shareholders took up their rights leaving investors china development bank and qatar investment authority with increased holdings in the bank barclays launched a further round of capital raising approved by special resolution on  november  as part of its overall plan to achieve higher capital targets set by the fsa to ensure it would remain independent barclays raised £ billion from investors from abu dhabi and qatar existing barclays shareholders complained they were not offered full preemption rights in this round of capital raising even threatening to revolt at the extraordinary meeting sheikh mansour and qatar holding agreed to open up £ million of their new holdings of reserve capital instruments for clawback existing investors now took this up in  barclays bought the credit card brand goldfish for us million gaining  million customers and us billion in receivables barclays also bought a controlling stake in the russian retail bank expobank for us million later in the year barclays commenced its pakistan operations with initial funding of us million lehman brothers acquisitionedit the former headquarters of lehman brothers in new york city now owned by barclays the new york building at night on  september  barclays announced its agreement to purchase subject to regulatory approval the investmentbanking and trading divisions of lehman brothers including its new york skyscraper which was a united states financial conglomerate that had filed for bankruptcy on  september  a revised version of the deal a us billion £ million plan for barclays plc to acquire the core business of lehman brothers mainly lehmans us million midtown manhattan office skyscraper with responsibility for  former employees was approved after a sevenhour hearing new york bankruptcy court judge james peck ruled i have to approve this transaction because it is the only available transaction lehman brothers became a victim in effect the only true icon to fall in a tsunami that has befallen the credit markets this is the most momentous bankruptcy hearing ive ever sat through it can never be deemed precedent for future cases its hard for me to imagine a similar emergency luc despins the creditors committee counsel said the reason were not objecting is really based on the lack of a viable alternative we did not support the transaction because there had not been enough time to properly review it in the amended agreement barclays would absorb us billion in securities and assume us billion in trading liabilities lehmans attorney harvey r miller of weil gotshal  manges said the purchase price for the real estate components of the deal would be us billion including us million for lehmans new york headquarters and us million for two new jersey data centers lehmans original estimate valued its headquarters at us billion but an appraisal from cb richard ellis this week valued it at us million further barclays will not acquire lehmans eagle energy unit but will have entities known as lehman brothers canada inc lehman brothers sudamerica lehman brothers uruguay and its private investment management business for highnetworth individuals finally lehman will retain us billion of securities assets in lehman brothers inc that are not being transferred to barclays barclays had a potential liability of us billion to be paid as severance if it chooses not to retain some lehman employees beyond the guaranteed  days in september  barclays was ordered to pay  million in settlement charges that alleged the bank had failed to maintain an adequate internal compliance system after its acquisition of lehman brothers during the  financial crisis  to presentedit the former headquarters of barclays global investors in san francisco united states barclays sold barclays global investors to blackrock in  reuters later reported that the british government would inject £ billion us billion into three banks including barclays which might seek over £ billion barclays later confirmed that it rejected the governments offer and would instead raise £ billion of new capital £ billion by cancellation of dividend and £ billion from private investors barclays share price fell  in june  after the international petroleum investment company ipic which had invested up to £ billion in november  sold  billion barclays shares qatar holding sold a  stake worth £ billion in october  and a further sale of warrants worth around £ million in november  but remains one of the banks largest shareholders in july  barclays revealed that the fsa was investigating whether the bank adequately disclosed fees paid to qatar investment authority in august  the serious fraud office announced an investigation into the middle east capital raising the financial services authority announced an expansion of the investigation into the barclaysqatar deal in january  focusing on the disclosure surrounding the ownership of the securities in the bank in january  the press reported that further capital may be required and that while the government might be willing to fund this it may be unable to do so because the previous capital investment from the qatari state was subject to a proviso that no third party might put in further money without the qataris receiving compensation at the value the shares had commanded in october  in march  it was reported that in  barclays received billions of dollars from its insurance arrangements with aig including us billion from funds provided by the united states to bail out aig