ys sold barclays bank of california which at that time was the thlargest bank in california measured by assets to wells fargo for us million in cash edgar pearce the mardi gra bomber began a terror campaign against the bank and the supermarket chain sainsburys in  in  barclays bought wells fargo nikko investment advisors wfnia and merged it with bzw investment management to form barclays global investors two years later in  the bzw business was broken up and parts were sold to credit suisse first boston barclays retained the debt business which formed the foundation of what is now barclays capital in  in an unusual move as part of the trend at the time for free isps barclays launched an internet service called barclaysnet this entity was acquired by british telecom in  in august  barclays took over the recently demutualised woolwich plc formerly the woolwich building society in a £bn acquisition woolwich plc thus joined the barclays group of companies and the woolwich name was retained after the acquisition the companys head office remained in bexleyheath southeast london four miles from the original head office in woolwich st centuryedit a barclays branch in stratforduponavon united kingdom in  barclays closed  branches in the uk many of them in rural communities barclays called itself the big bank but this name was quickly given a low profile after a series of embarrassing pr stunts in  barclays bought the american credit card company juniper bank from cibc rebranding it as barclays bank delaware the same year saw the acquisition of banco zaragozano the th largest spanish bank barclays took over sponsorship of the premier league from barclaycard in  in may  barclays moved its group headquarters from lombard street in the city of london to one churchill place in canary wharf also in  barclays sealed a £bn takeover of absa group limited south africas largest retail bank acquiring a  stake on  july  then in  barclays purchased the homeq servicing corporation for us m