s lse barc nyse bcs ftse  component industry banking financial services founded  november   years ago  in london kingdom of england headquarters london e united kingdom area served worldwide key people john mcfarlane chairman jes staley group chief executive products retail banking commercial banking investment banking investment management revenue £ billion  operating income £ billion  profit £ billion  total assets £ trillion  total equity £ billion  number of employees   divisions barclaycard barclays investment bank barclays wealth subsidiaries barclays africa group barclays bank website wwwhomebarclays wwwarchivebarclayscom barclays ˈbɑːrkliz is a british multinational bank and financial services company headquartered in london it is a universal bank with operations in retail wholesale and investment banking as well as wealth management mortgage lending and credit cards it has operations in over  countries and territories and has around  million customers barclays is organised into four core businesses personal  corporate personal banking corporate banking wealth  investment management barclaycard investment banking and africa barclays traces its origins to a goldsmith banking business established in the city of london in  james barclay became a partner in the business in  in  several banks in london and the english provinces including backhouses bank and gurneys bank united as a jointstock bank under the name barclays and co over the following decades barclays expanded to become a nationwide bank in  barclays deployed the worlds first cash dispenser barclays has made numerous corporate acquisitions including of london provincial and south western bank in  british linen bank in  mercantile credit in  the woolwich in  and the north american operations of lehman brothers in  barclays has a primary listing on the london stock exchange and is a constituent of the ftse  index it has a secondary listing on the new york stock exchange according to a  paper by vitali et al barclays was the most powerful transnational corporation in terms of ownership and thus corporate control over global financial stability and market competition with axa and state street corporation taking the nd and rd position respectively contents  history   to    to    to    to   st century  abandoned merger with abn amro  financing  lehman brothers acquisition   to present  operations  principal divisions and subsidiaries  branches and atms  senior management  executive committee  board of directors  sponsorships  controversies  involvement with south africa under apartheid  financial support for the government in zimbabwe  accusations of money laundering  senior management bonuses  tax avoidance   tax repayment  conflicts of interest  customer satisfaction  ratefixing scandal  staff diversity  qatari capital raising regulatory investigations  us electricity market manipulation  gold price manipulation  us lawsuit alleging dark pool fraud  exchangerate rigging last look system  unsuitable mutual fund transactions  bibliography  see also  notes  references  external links historyedit  to edit barclays traces its origins back to  when john freame a quaker and thomas gould started trading as goldsmith bankers in lombard street london the name barclays became associated with the business in  when james barclay the soninlaw of john freame one of the founders became a partner in the business in  the bank moved to  lombard street identified by the sign of the black spread eagle which in subsequent years would become a core part of the banks visual identity much of the wealth of the barclay family was founded on the slave trade david and alexander barclay were engaged in the slave trade in  david barclay owned a great plantation in jamaica later freeing his slaves and coming to appreciate their equivalence to whites in  the firm was styled barclay bevan and bening and so remained until  when another partner john tritton who had married a barclay was admitted and the business then became barclay bevan bening and tritton in  several banks in london and the english provinces notably backhouses bank of darlington and gurneys bank of norwich united under the banner of barclays and co a jointstock bank  to edit the barclays bank branch in sutton london which was originally a branch of london and provincial prior to acquisition by barclays between  and  barclays extended its branch network by making acquisitions of small english banks further expansion followed in  when barclays amalgamated with the london provincial and south western bank and in  when the british linen bank was acquired by barclays bank although the british linen bank retained a separate board of directors and continued to issue its own bank notes see banknotes of the pound sterling in  the colonial bank national bank of south africa and the angloegyptian bank were amalgamated and barclays operated its overseas operations under the name barclays bank dominion colonial and overseas – barclays dco in  barclays acquired the first indian exchange bank the central exchange bank of india which had opened in london in  with the sponsorship of central bank of india  to edit in may  barclays was the first uk bank to appoint a female bank manager hilda harding managed barclays hanover square branch in london until her retirement in  a plaque in enfield united kingdom commemorating the installation of the worlds first cash machine by barclays in  in  barclays established a us affiliate barclays bank of california in san francisco barclays launched the first credit card in the uk barclaycard in  on  june  barclays deployed the worlds first cash machine in enfield the british actor reg varney was the first person to use the machine in  a planned merger with martins bank and lloyds bank was blocked by the monopolies and mergers commission but the acquisition of martins bank on its own was later permitted also that year the british linen bank subsidiary was sold to the bank of scotland in exchange for a  stake a transaction that became effective from  barclays dco changed its name to barclays bank international in  in august  following the secondary banking crash barclays acquired mercantile credit company  to edit in  barclays bank international expanded its business to include commercial credit and took over american credit corporation renaming it barclays american corporation the following year barclays bank and barclays bank international merged and as part of the corporate reorganization the former barclays bank plc became a group holding company renamed barclays plc and uk retail banking was integrated under the former bbi and renamed barclays bank plc from barclays bank limited in  barclays sold its south african business operating under the barclays national bank name after protests against barclays involvement in south africa and its apartheid government also that year barclays bought de zoete  bevan and wedd durlacher formerly wedd jefferson to form barclays de zoete wedd bzw now known as the barclays investment bank and to take advantage of the big bang on the london stock exchange barclays introduced the connect card in june  the first debit card in the united kingdom in  barclays sold barclays bank of california which at that time was the thlargest bank in california measured by assets to wells fargo for us million in cash edgar pearce the mardi gra bomber began a terror campaign against the bank and the supermarket chain sainsburys in  in  barclays bought wells fargo nikko investment advisors wfnia and merged it with bzw investment management to form barclays global investors two years later in  the bzw business was broken up and parts were sold to credit suisse first boston barclays retained the debt business which formed the foundation of what is now barclays capital in  in an unusual move as part of the trend at the time for free isps barclays launched an internet service called barclaysnet this entity was acquired by british telecom in  in august  barclays took over the recently demutualised woolwich plc formerly the woolwich building society in a £bn acquisition woolwich plc thus joined the barclays group of companies and the woolwich name was retained after the acquisition the companys head office remained in bexleyheath southeast london four miles from the original head office in woolwich st centuryedit a barclays branch in stratforduponavon united kingdom in  barclays closed  branches in the uk many of them in rural communities barclays called itself the big bank but this name was quickly given a low profile after a series of embarrassing pr stunts in  barclays bought the american credit card company juniper bank from cibc rebranding it as barclays bank delaware the same year saw the acquisition of banco zaragozano the th largest spanish bank barclays took over sponsorship of the premier league from barclaycard in  in may  barclays moved its group headquarters from lombard street in the city of london to one churchill place in canary wharf also in  barclays sealed a £bn takeover of absa group limited south africas largest retail bank acquiring a  stake on  july  then in  barclays purchased the homeq servicing corporation for us million in cash from wachovia corp that year also saw the acquisition of the financial website comparetheloan and barclays announcing plans to rebrand woolwich branches as barclays migrating woolwich customers onto barclays accounts and migrating backoffice processes onto barclays systems – the woolwich brand was to be used for barclays mortgages in january  barclays announced that it had purchased the naming rights to the barclays center a proposed seat arena in brooklyn new york where the new jersey nets planned to relocate abandoned merger with abn amroedit in march  barclays announced plans to merge with abn amro the largest bank in the netherlands however on  october  barclays announced that it had abandoned its bid citing inadequate support by abn shareholders fewer than  of shares had been tendered to barclays cashandshares offer this left the consortium led by royal bank of scotland free to proceed with its us cents counterbid for abn amro to help finance its bid for abn amro barclays sold a  stake to china development bank and a  stake to temasek holdings the investment arm of the singaporean government also in  barclays agreed to purchase equifirst corporation from regions financial corporation for us million that year also saw barclays personal investment management announcing the closure of their operation in peterborough and its resiting to glasgow laying off nearly  members of staff financingedit on  august  barclays was forced to borrow £ billion us billion from the bank of england sterling standby facility this is made available as a lastresort when banks are unable to settle their debts to other banks at the end of daily trading despite rumours about liquidity at barclays the loan was necessary due to a technical problem with their computerised settlement network a barclays spokesman was quoted as saying there are no liquidity issues in the uk markets barclays itself is flush with liquidity on  november  barclays shares dropped  and were even temporarily suspended for a short period of time due to rumours of a £ billion us billion exposure to bad debts in the us however a barclays spokesman denied the rumours barclays sought to raise capital privately avoiding direct equity investment from the uk government which was offered to boost its capital ratio barclays believed that maintaining its independence from government was in the best interests of its shareholders in july  barclays attempted to raise £ billion through a nontraditional rights issue to shore up its weakened tier  capital ratio which involved a rights offer to existing shareholders and the sale of a stake to sumitomo mitsui banking corporation only  of shareholders took up their rights leaving investors china development bank and qatar investment authority with increased holdings in the bank barclays launched a further round of capital raising approved by special resolution on  november  as part of its overall plan to achieve higher capital targets set by the fsa to ensure it would remain independent barclays raised £ billion from investors from abu dhabi and qatar existing barclays shareholders complained they were not offered full preemption rights in this round of capital raising even threatening to revolt at the extraordinary meeting sheikh mansour and qatar holding agreed to open up £ million of their new holdings of reserve capital instruments for clawback existing investors now took this up in  barclays bought the credit card brand goldfish for us million gaining  million customers and us billion in receivables barclays also bought a controlling stake in the russian retail bank expobank for us million later in the year barclays commenced its pakistan operations with initial funding of us million lehman brothers acquisitionedit the former headquarters of lehman brothers in new york city now owned by barclays the new york building at night on  september  barclays announced its agreement to purchase subject to regulatory approval the investmentbanking and trading divisions of lehman brothers including its new york skyscraper which was a united states financial conglomerate that had filed for bankruptcy on  september  a revised version of the deal a us billion £ million plan for barclays plc to acquire the core business of lehman brothers mainly lehmans us million midtown manhattan office skyscraper with responsibility for  former employees was approved after a sevenhour hearing new york bankruptcy court judge james peck ruled i have to approve this transaction because it is the only available transaction lehman brothers became a victim in effect the only true icon to fall in a tsunami that has befallen the credit markets this is the most momentous bankruptcy hearing ive ever sat through it can never be deemed precedent for future cases its hard for me to imagine a similar emergency luc despins the creditors committee counsel said the reason were not objecting is really based on the lack of a viable alternative we did not support the transaction because there had not been enough time to properly review it in the amended agreement barclays would absorb us billion in securities and assume us billion in trading liabilities lehmans attorney harvey r miller of weil gotshal  manges said the purchase price for the real estate components of the deal would be us billion including us million for lehmans new york headquarters and us million for two new jersey data centers lehmans original estimate valued its headquarters at us billion but an appraisal from cb richard ellis this week valued it at us million further barclays will not acquire lehmans eagle energy unit but will have entities known as lehman brothers canada inc lehman brothers sudamerica lehman brothers uruguay and its private investment management business for highnetworth individuals finally lehman will retain us billion of securities assets in lehman brothers inc that are not being transferred to barclays barclays had a potential liability of us billion to be paid as severance if it chooses not to retain some lehman employees beyond the guaranteed  days in september  barclays was ordered to pay  million in settlement charges that alleged the bank had failed to maintain an adequate internal compliance system after its acquisition of lehman brothers during the  financial crisis  to presentedit the former headquarters of barclays global investors in san francisco united states barclays sold barclays global investors to blackrock in  reuters later reported that the british government would inject £ billion us billion into three banks including barclays which might seek over £ billion barclays later confirmed that it rejected the governments offer and would instead raise £ billion of new capital £ billion by cancellation of dividend and £ billion from private investors barclays share price fell  in june  after the international petroleum investment company ipic which had invested up to £ billion in november  sold  billion barclays shares qatar holding sold a  stake worth £ billion in october  and a further sale of warrants worth around £ million in november  but remains one of the banks largest shareholders in july  barclays revealed that the fsa was investigating whether the bank adequately disclosed fees paid to qatar investment authority in august  the serious fraud office announced an investigation into the middle east capital raising the financial services authority announced an expansion of the investigation into the barclaysqatar deal in january  focusing on the disclosure surrounding the ownership of the securities in the bank in january  the press reported that further capital may be required and that while the government might be willing to fund this it may be unable to do so because the previous capital investment from the qatari state was subject to a proviso that no third party might put in further money without the qataris receiving compensation at the value the shares had commanded in october  in march  it was reported that in  barclays received billions of dollars from its insurance arrangements with aig including us billion from funds provided by the united states to bail out aig on  june  barclays sold its global investors unit which included its exchange traded fund business ishares to blackrock for us billion standard life sold standard life bank plc to barclays plc in october  the sale was completed on  january  on  november  barclays and first data a global technology provider of information commerce had entered into an agreement according to which barclays would migrate a range of card portfolios to first datas issuing and consumer finance platform on  february  barclays announced it would pay more than £ billion in bonuses in march  it was reported that barclays had overtaken santander uk to claim top spot as the uks most complained against bank with the countrys official banking regulator the financial services authority having recorded  new customer complaints against barclays bank during the second half of  barclays nevertheless ranks only third in the uk among the mainstream clearing banks in terms of the number of its branches inline with costs cut barclays cut  jobs during the first half of  and cut another  jobs for the rest of  in march  the trading names of barclays capital barclays wealth and barclays corporate were each changed to simply barclays as part of an effort to simplify the operations of the company and to promote greater integration between its divisions in june  barclaycard acquired analog analytics a digital coupon and daily deal business similar to groupon in october  barclays announced it had agreed to buy the ing direct uk business of the ing group the transfer of the business to barclays was approved at the high court on  february  and ing direct was renamed barclays direct and will be integrated into the existing barclays business within two years in february  barclays announced a net loss of £ billion for  its first annual loss in two decades together with plans to cut  jobs reduce annual costs by £ billion and scale back its retail banking activities in europe and asia in may  barclays announced they would cut  jobs over  years with  jobs cut in  investment banking will cut  jobs in  and up to  jobs totally in  making the investment banking portion shrink from  percent in  to  percent of barclays assets in  barclays announced in june  that it would sell its us wealth and investment management business to stifel for an undisclosed fee barclays sold its retail banking unit in spain to caixabank in  at its peak barclays had  employees and  offices in spain in  the bank had  employees and  offices with the sale caixabank acquired around  new retail and private banking clients an